1
00:00:36,500 --> 00:00:37,767
<i>My suspicions were right
all along.</i>

2
00:00:37,900 --> 00:00:39,367
<i> But where did you get this?</i>

3
00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:43,067
<i>Did you plant a hidden camera
in Aunt Felma's house?</i>

4
00:00:43,200 --> 00:00:44,100
<i> Jessica, what's this?</i>

5
00:00:44,233 --> 00:00:45,467
<i> Son, is there a problem?</i>

6
00:00:45,600 --> 00:00:46,500
<i> It's about Daisy.</i>

7
00:00:46,633 --> 00:00:47,767
<i>I thought
that once we were together,</i>

8
00:00:47,900 --> 00:00:49,767
<i>we'd be happy, and everything
would fall into place.</i>

9
00:00:49,900 --> 00:00:51,133
<i> You know, like...</i>

10
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:52,100
<i> Like?</i>

11
00:00:52,233 --> 00:00:53,767
<i> Like you and your ex.</i>

12
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:54,833
<i> Mom planted it.</i>

13
00:00:54,967 --> 00:00:56,567
<i>How did you know
there was a camera?</i>

14
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:58,000
<i> Did you meet with your mom?</i>

15
00:00:58,133 --> 00:01:02,233
<i>She showed me a video
of you and Aunt Felma kissing.</i>

16
00:01:02,367 --> 00:01:03,700
<i> Is Aunt Felma your mistress?</i>

17
00:01:03,833 --> 00:01:05,133
<i> Take back what you said!</i>

18
00:01:05,267 --> 00:01:06,167
<i> Coleen, stop!</i>

19
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:07,800
<i>- Coleen!
- Jessica!</i>

20
00:01:07,967 --> 00:01:09,900
<i> She called you a mistress.</i>

21
00:01:10,033 --> 00:01:12,067
<i>I didn't call Aunt Felma
a mistress.</i>

22
00:01:12,200 --> 00:01:13,367
<i> I was asking Dad.</i>

23
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:14,500
<i>You still entertained
the thought</i>

24
00:01:14,633 --> 00:01:15,633
<i> that Felma is my mistress!</i>

25
00:01:15,767 --> 00:01:17,200
<i> I won't let you call her that!</i>

26
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:19,200
<i> I'm sorry, Aunt Felma.</i>

27
00:01:19,333 --> 00:01:20,000
<i> Give it to me!</i>

28
00:01:20,133 --> 00:01:21,400
<i>Is this what you're looking for?</i>

29
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:22,667
<i> Traitor!</i>

30
00:01:22,800 --> 00:01:24,200
<i> Hazel, stop!</i>

31
00:01:24,333 --> 00:01:25,267
<i> Mom!</i>

32
00:01:27,467 --> 00:01:28,867
<i> You've gone too far!</i>

33
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,533
<i> I can't take you anymore!</i>

34
00:01:30,667 --> 00:01:31,867
<i> Jessica!</i>

35
00:01:32,000 --> 00:01:33,967
<i> You still love Aunt Felma.</i>

36
00:01:34,100 --> 00:01:37,867
<i>I didn't deny it
because it's true.</i>

37
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:39,833
<i> I still love Felma.</i>

38
00:01:43,100 --> 00:01:45,933
I'm the only one who
remains in love.

39
00:01:46,067 --> 00:01:48,367
Whatever she's feeling
for me right now...

40
00:01:48,500 --> 00:01:49,600
maybe...

41
00:01:50,600 --> 00:01:51,933
it's just pity.

42
00:01:52,067 --> 00:01:53,467
Not love.

43
00:01:54,667 --> 00:01:58,733
Because she only sees me
as a friend now.

44
00:01:58,867 --> 00:02:01,400
She wants to keep
the family whole, sure.

45
00:02:01,533 --> 00:02:03,700
But not as...

46
00:02:03,833 --> 00:02:05,733
husband and wife.

47
00:02:06,633 --> 00:02:09,267
Just as co-parents
for the children.

48
00:02:11,800 --> 00:02:13,300
You know what.

49
00:02:13,433 --> 00:02:14,500
Dear...

50
00:02:16,333 --> 00:02:17,333
Honestly,

51
00:02:18,300 --> 00:02:20,567
I always pray that...

52
00:02:22,033 --> 00:02:24,533
these feelings
would just go away.

53
00:02:25,600 --> 00:02:29,300
Because the woman I love
is within my reach.

54
00:02:33,067 --> 00:02:35,000
She's so near.

55
00:02:36,867 --> 00:02:39,167
But I can't love her.

56
00:03:05,033 --> 00:03:07,600
Hi, Ma'am Felma.
I've already fixed the...

57
00:03:09,233 --> 00:03:10,033
Ma'am...

58
00:03:10,167 --> 00:03:11,267
Ma'am, what's wrong?

59
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:12,033
Ma'am...

60
00:03:12,167 --> 00:03:13,800
Ma'am Felma!

61
00:03:15,700 --> 00:03:16,733
I'm sorry.

62
00:03:17,667 --> 00:03:20,600
I shouldn't be telling you this.

63
00:03:20,767 --> 00:03:22,633
It's wrong for me to tell you...

64
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:26,733
about the woman I love,

65
00:03:26,867 --> 00:03:28,667
who isn't your mom.

66
00:03:30,500 --> 00:03:33,167
You were just telling
your truth, Dad.

67
00:03:35,267 --> 00:03:36,633
You're not mad?

68
00:03:38,533 --> 00:03:43,067
I can't be mad at you for loving
the woman you truly loved.

69
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,567
It's your feelings, Dad.

70
00:03:46,700 --> 00:03:49,133
And I can't blame
you for feeling that.

71
00:03:51,200 --> 00:03:53,967
Because I saw the difference...

72
00:03:55,433 --> 00:03:57,767
in the way Mom treats you

73
00:03:57,900 --> 00:03:59,767
and the way Aunt Felma does.

74
00:04:01,367 --> 00:04:03,100
And to think that...

75
00:04:03,233 --> 00:04:08,700
what I see now is how she treats
you as a friend.

76
00:04:08,833 --> 00:04:11,600
What more
when you were still together?

77
00:04:14,567 --> 00:04:16,000
Dad,

78
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:18,033
you did everything.

79
00:04:19,533 --> 00:04:21,600
All those years,

80
00:04:21,733 --> 00:04:24,267
you stayed with Mom.

81
00:04:24,400 --> 00:04:26,833
You committed your life to her,

82
00:04:27,000 --> 00:04:29,567
and you tried to love her.

83
00:04:29,700 --> 00:04:32,300
But Dad, let's be honest.

84
00:04:32,433 --> 00:04:34,700
She's so hard to love.

85
00:04:36,733 --> 00:04:38,133
Is it really okay with you?

86
00:04:40,000 --> 00:04:42,733
I may sound like a bad
daughter for saying this.

87
00:04:45,067 --> 00:04:46,333
But yes.

88
00:04:48,700 --> 00:04:51,233
I'll be happy...

89
00:04:51,367 --> 00:04:53,067
with whatever makes you happy.

90
00:04:53,200 --> 00:04:55,533
But why were you mad...

91
00:04:55,667 --> 00:04:59,200
when you asked me if something's
going on between Felma and me?

92
00:04:59,333 --> 00:05:01,567
Dad, I wasn't mad.

93
00:05:03,467 --> 00:05:05,200
I was scared.

94
00:05:05,333 --> 00:05:07,467
You all misunderstood me.

95
00:05:08,433 --> 00:05:10,600
I'm scared because...

96
00:05:10,733 --> 00:05:13,033
Mom will have you jailed

97
00:05:13,167 --> 00:05:16,567
if it's true you're having
an affair with Aunt Felma.

98
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,767
Dad,

99
00:05:18,767 --> 00:05:21,500
she's still your wife.

100
00:05:21,633 --> 00:05:23,400
I don't want you to get jailed.

101
00:05:25,400 --> 00:05:27,533
Don't worry, sweetie.

102
00:05:27,667 --> 00:05:30,533
That won't happen.

103
00:05:30,667 --> 00:05:33,000
Yes, I love Felma.
I love her so much.

104
00:05:34,733 --> 00:05:36,267
But we can never
get back together.

105
00:05:38,467 --> 00:05:40,833
Because we're leaving.

106
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:50,200
Yes, Miles.

107
00:05:50,333 --> 00:05:52,067
The HR has already called me.

108
00:05:52,200 --> 00:05:56,900
Hey, thank you so much for
helping me get the job.

109
00:05:57,033 --> 00:05:58,967
See you soon. Bye.

110
00:06:02,167 --> 00:06:03,533
Hazel.

111
00:06:03,667 --> 00:06:06,000
Hey, wait.

112
00:06:06,133 --> 00:06:07,300
It's so early.

113
00:06:07,467 --> 00:06:09,400
It's so early to be in such
a mood. What happened to you?

114
00:06:09,533 --> 00:06:11,600
Is it about Felma again?

115
00:06:11,733 --> 00:06:13,233
Yes!

116
00:06:13,367 --> 00:06:15,800
Darn that woman!

117
00:06:15,933 --> 00:06:17,800
She stormed into the hospital
last night...

118
00:06:17,933 --> 00:06:19,333
with Jessica.

119
00:06:20,467 --> 00:06:21,667
And Jessica...

120
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:24,567
Jessica hurt me.

121
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:29,200
- She pushed me.
- Oh, my god.

122
00:06:29,333 --> 00:06:31,633
So that's how it is, huh?

123
00:06:31,767 --> 00:06:35,167
So that's what it feels like
when your own child hurts you.

124
00:06:35,300 --> 00:06:37,167
It's not my physical body that
was hurt.

125
00:06:38,400 --> 00:06:39,667
But my heart.

126
00:06:44,567 --> 00:06:46,833
That Felma has really drained
all my patience.

127
00:06:46,967 --> 00:06:49,433
I'll push through
with the lawsuit.

128
00:06:49,567 --> 00:06:51,400
What's your proof?

129
00:06:51,533 --> 00:06:53,267
The video
where nothing happened?

130
00:06:53,400 --> 00:06:55,467
And you illegally took?

131
00:06:55,600 --> 00:06:57,467
Friend, you don't stand
a chance against them.

132
00:06:58,733 --> 00:07:00,167
Not yet.

133
00:07:01,900 --> 00:07:04,133
But I'll find a way.

134
00:07:04,267 --> 00:07:07,600
Your concubinage case
won't hold up.

135
00:07:07,733 --> 00:07:09,033
Fine.

136
00:07:09,167 --> 00:07:11,367
Let's say,
by some divine intervention,

137
00:07:11,500 --> 00:07:13,633
you stumble upon evidence.

138
00:07:13,800 --> 00:07:16,600
Only Manuel will go to jail,
not Felma.

139
00:07:16,733 --> 00:07:21,500
Do you want your own child
to curse you forever?

140
00:07:21,633 --> 00:07:25,500
I need to find a way
to control Jessica.

141
00:07:25,633 --> 00:07:27,100
So that...

142
00:07:27,233 --> 00:07:29,067
Manuel will be forced
to come back to me.

143
00:07:30,033 --> 00:07:31,167
How?

144
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:33,933
The videos in my spy camera...

145
00:07:35,667 --> 00:07:37,367
I haven't reviewed all yet.

146
00:07:37,500 --> 00:07:40,933
Maybe I can find something
I can use against them.

147
00:08:04,000 --> 00:08:05,067
My god, sis.

148
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:08,000
Jessica and Coleen's fights
just keep getting worse.

149
00:08:08,133 --> 00:08:11,100
And that troublemaker went as
far as planting a camera,

150
00:08:11,233 --> 00:08:13,700
and now
there's a lawsuit threat.

151
00:08:13,833 --> 00:08:14,967
Sis...

152
00:08:15,100 --> 00:08:17,867
if every problem
paid out in cash,

153
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:20,400
you'd be living the millionaire
contractor life.

154
00:08:23,267 --> 00:08:24,367
You know what, friend?

155
00:08:24,500 --> 00:08:28,000
I think there's only one
solution to all your problems.

156
00:08:28,133 --> 00:08:30,267
Let your boarders go.

157
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:32,400
Ever since they moved
into your house,

158
00:08:32,533 --> 00:08:35,300
your problems
have never stopped.

159
00:08:36,333 --> 00:08:37,267
Sis,

160
00:08:37,400 --> 00:08:40,900
don't blame everything
on Manuel and Jessica.

161
00:08:41,033 --> 00:08:42,467
Who should I blame instead?

162
00:08:42,600 --> 00:08:44,200
Should I blame the lizard
on the ceiling?

163
00:08:44,333 --> 00:08:45,467
The bystander
on the corner street?

164
00:08:45,600 --> 00:08:47,633
Who do I even blame?
Aren't they the problem?

165
00:08:47,767 --> 00:08:52,200
The queen of troublemakers
keeps starting wars with you

166
00:08:52,333 --> 00:08:53,667
because of them.

167
00:08:53,800 --> 00:08:54,967
Friend...

168
00:08:55,133 --> 00:08:58,500
why can't you let them go?

169
00:08:58,633 --> 00:09:00,600
You know why.

170
00:09:00,733 --> 00:09:02,100
I want...

171
00:09:02,233 --> 00:09:07,600
Jeffrey and Andrea to come
home and find their dad there.

172
00:09:07,733 --> 00:09:10,233
I've memorized that, sis.

173
00:09:10,367 --> 00:09:13,067
You know what, sis? I've already
given up on the dream

174
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:15,800
that they'll ever forgive
each other.

175
00:09:15,933 --> 00:09:17,467
Sis, come on.
A lot has already happened.

176
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:22,333
You and Jepoy have already
forgiven each other.

177
00:09:22,467 --> 00:09:24,600
But where are they now?

178
00:09:24,733 --> 00:09:27,500
Andrea doesn't want
to come home. Right?

179
00:09:27,667 --> 00:09:28,633
Sis,

180
00:09:28,767 --> 00:09:30,533
I'm giving you a real talk.

181
00:09:31,833 --> 00:09:35,267
What's the real reason
for not letting go of Manuel?

182
00:09:35,400 --> 00:09:37,233
Is it really for the kids?

183
00:09:37,367 --> 00:09:39,233
Or for you?

184
00:09:46,533 --> 00:09:49,567
<i>I asked you before
if you love her.</i>

185
00:09:49,700 --> 00:09:51,600
<i> You didn't deny it.</i>

186
00:09:51,733 --> 00:09:53,667
<i> I didn't deny because...</i>

187
00:09:54,600 --> 00:09:55,967
<i> it's true.</i>

188
00:09:57,633 --> 00:09:59,433
<i> I still love Felma.</i>

189
00:10:01,967 --> 00:10:05,533
You know, I also know very well
when you're acting like that.

190
00:10:05,667 --> 00:10:07,967
There's something you're not
telling me. Is that right?

191
00:10:09,000 --> 00:10:10,300
Nothing.

192
00:10:10,433 --> 00:10:11,300
Please.

193
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,067
Do what I told you to do.

194
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:14,667
It's been hours already.

195
00:10:14,800 --> 00:10:16,533
Oh, yeah.

196
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:18,933
Sorry, Ma'am. I'll do it now.

197
00:10:21,600 --> 00:10:23,800
But I'll come back
for the answer.

198
00:10:41,900 --> 00:10:44,033
Here's your hot coffee, Sir.

199
00:10:44,167 --> 00:10:45,200
Thank you.

200
00:10:47,833 --> 00:10:48,900
Sir Manuel,

201
00:10:49,033 --> 00:10:52,067
I didn't mean to pry.

202
00:10:52,200 --> 00:10:54,467
I'm already involved anyway.

203
00:10:54,600 --> 00:10:58,500
And you treat me
like family, too.

204
00:10:58,633 --> 00:11:00,933
Why did you make
Ma'am Felma cry?

205
00:11:03,533 --> 00:11:04,700
She cried?

206
00:11:04,833 --> 00:11:05,867
Yes.

207
00:11:06,000 --> 00:11:10,367
I saw her last night,
peeking into your room, crying.

208
00:11:10,533 --> 00:11:12,300
Then I followed her
when she left your room.

209
00:11:12,433 --> 00:11:13,800
I asked what happened.

210
00:11:13,933 --> 00:11:15,733
But she ignored me.

211
00:11:17,033 --> 00:11:17,867
She cried?

212
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:20,767
Yes. You keep asking
the same question.

213
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:22,033
She cried.

214
00:11:22,167 --> 00:11:23,700
What did you do?

215
00:11:23,833 --> 00:11:26,700
Why do I feel like
she's really confused?

216
00:11:27,933 --> 00:11:29,800
<i> Did she hear what I said?</i>

217
00:11:31,433 --> 00:11:35,067
And she told me to give
this back to Jessica.

218
00:11:37,367 --> 00:11:38,533
Sir.

219
00:11:38,667 --> 00:11:40,000
Sir Manuel.

220
00:11:40,133 --> 00:11:41,867
Sir.

221
00:11:42,033 --> 00:11:44,033
She wants Jessica to have this.

222
00:11:47,667 --> 00:11:50,767
I'll come back for your answer,
okay?

223
00:11:50,900 --> 00:11:53,233
Someone's ringing the doorbell.
I'll be right back, Sir.

224
00:12:10,933 --> 00:12:12,667
Jessica!

225
00:12:12,800 --> 00:12:14,867
Dear.

226
00:12:15,033 --> 00:12:16,933
Mom.

227
00:12:17,067 --> 00:12:18,967
Dear. I'm so happy to see you.

228
00:12:20,033 --> 00:12:21,300
Dear.

229
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,767
I know you're still upset
with me

230
00:12:26,900 --> 00:12:29,067
because of what happened
last night.

231
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:31,333
But, dear, you can't blame me.

232
00:12:31,467 --> 00:12:34,633
Why did you even have
to bring Felma?

233
00:12:34,767 --> 00:12:36,167
Mom, what are you doing here?

234
00:12:37,533 --> 00:12:39,467
I only want to see you.

235
00:12:39,600 --> 00:12:40,767
You know...

236
00:12:40,900 --> 00:12:44,267
I was really hoping
that you'd pass by.

237
00:12:44,400 --> 00:12:47,167
That you'd go out
of the village.

238
00:12:47,300 --> 00:12:49,533
And thank God I saw you.

239
00:12:51,333 --> 00:12:52,767
Mom, what do you want?

240
00:12:52,900 --> 00:12:54,700
If you're here
to make trouble...

241
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:56,000
No.

242
00:12:56,133 --> 00:12:57,767
I only want to talk to you.

243
00:12:58,833 --> 00:13:01,167
Whatever that is,
please say it now.

244
00:13:03,100 --> 00:13:04,100
Dear,

245
00:13:05,633 --> 00:13:08,700
can you...

246
00:13:08,833 --> 00:13:09,900
come back to me?

247
00:13:11,500 --> 00:13:13,333
Please come back to me.

248
00:13:13,467 --> 00:13:14,867
You and your Dad.

249
00:13:15,833 --> 00:13:17,500
You know?

250
00:13:17,633 --> 00:13:20,000
You're not truly welcome there.

251
00:13:20,133 --> 00:13:21,867
That's not true!

252
00:13:22,033 --> 00:13:25,633
Aunt Felma and Coleen
welcome me with open arms.

253
00:13:25,767 --> 00:13:28,133
Felma, yes. Maybe.

254
00:13:28,267 --> 00:13:31,133
She's forced
to accept you for Manuel.

255
00:13:32,700 --> 00:13:33,667
But Coleen?

256
00:13:35,167 --> 00:13:36,067
No.

257
00:13:37,100 --> 00:13:39,433
Dear, I have proof.

258
00:13:39,567 --> 00:13:42,233
The videos from
the spy camera.

259
00:13:44,367 --> 00:13:45,433
Look.

260
00:13:51,367 --> 00:13:53,567
Those are the videos
from the spy camera.

261
00:13:53,700 --> 00:13:55,233
<i> We made Mom angry again.</i>

262
00:13:55,400 --> 00:13:57,267
<i> That was Jessica's fault.</i>

263
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,367
<i>She keeps sticking her
nose into everything.</i>

264
00:13:59,500 --> 00:14:00,600
<i>She's not even part
of the family,</i>

265
00:14:00,733 --> 00:14:02,500
<i>but she keeps getting involved.</i>

266
00:14:02,633 --> 00:14:04,133
<i>You used to be
partners in crime.</i>

267
00:14:04,267 --> 00:14:05,533
<i> What happened?</i>

268
00:14:05,667 --> 00:14:06,600
<i> Before, yes.</i>

269
00:14:06,733 --> 00:14:09,033
<i>But she's become
too meddlesome.</i>

270
00:14:09,167 --> 00:14:11,067
<i> She's taking Mom away from me.</i>

271
00:14:11,200 --> 00:14:13,567
<i> She couldn't be content, Jeff.</i>

272
00:14:13,700 --> 00:14:15,233
<i> First, it was Dad.</i>

273
00:14:15,367 --> 00:14:17,200
<i>And now she's taking
away Mom, too.</i>

274
00:14:18,133 --> 00:14:19,600
<i>So, you no longer
welcome her?</i>

275
00:14:19,733 --> 00:14:22,167
<i>How can I welcome someone who's
taking everything I've got?</i>

276
00:14:23,433 --> 00:14:25,400
<i>She'd better go back to her mom</i>

277
00:14:25,533 --> 00:14:27,767
<i> and leave Dad here.</i>

278
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,867
How could Coleen
say those things?

279
00:14:46,000 --> 00:14:49,167
Mom, I'm not doing anything
to her.

280
00:14:49,300 --> 00:14:51,100
I didn't steal Dad from her.

281
00:14:51,233 --> 00:14:54,733
I even helped them meet.

282
00:14:54,867 --> 00:14:57,967
Dear, I couldn't believe it,
either.

283
00:14:58,100 --> 00:14:59,433
But...

284
00:14:59,567 --> 00:15:03,633
it's clear that she just used
you to get close to your Dad.

285
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:06,633
And now that they're together...

286
00:15:06,767 --> 00:15:08,433
you've become useless

287
00:15:08,567 --> 00:15:09,933
She wants you out.

288
00:15:12,067 --> 00:15:13,467
Okay.

289
00:15:13,600 --> 00:15:14,433
Stop crying.

290
00:15:14,567 --> 00:15:15,800
That's enough, dear.

291
00:15:15,933 --> 00:15:17,533
Maybe it's better
that we learned early on

292
00:15:17,667 --> 00:15:19,000
that they never wanted you.

293
00:15:20,467 --> 00:15:23,133
Felma's family doesn't want you.

294
00:15:23,267 --> 00:15:25,500
If I were you, dear,

295
00:15:25,633 --> 00:15:28,700
I wouldn't push myself on them.

296
00:15:28,833 --> 00:15:30,700
They're not
your siblings anyway.

297
00:15:33,700 --> 00:15:35,067
Mom!

298
00:15:39,433 --> 00:15:42,033
Nice. It's beautiful, bro.

299
00:15:42,167 --> 00:15:45,133
Good, now I've got something
I can use.

300
00:15:46,833 --> 00:15:48,567
How much do I owe you?

301
00:15:48,700 --> 00:15:49,600
Nothing.

302
00:15:49,733 --> 00:15:52,467
Come on.
It doesn't cost that much.

303
00:15:52,600 --> 00:15:53,733
Wow, you're so generous.

304
00:15:53,867 --> 00:15:58,700
So you don't have to borrow
Jessica's phone or Didang's.

305
00:15:58,833 --> 00:16:00,800
Nice. Thank you, bro.

306
00:16:02,167 --> 00:16:04,433
But...

307
00:16:04,567 --> 00:16:05,933
about what you said.

308
00:16:07,167 --> 00:16:09,633
Are you and Jessica
really leaving this house?

309
00:16:09,800 --> 00:16:13,567
Can't you wait
for your children's return?

310
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:15,533
I don't think it's possible,
bro.

311
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:20,133
Looks like they'll never come
back as long as I'm here.

312
00:16:21,733 --> 00:16:23,933
Maybe Felma and I got it wrong,
but...

313
00:16:25,533 --> 00:16:27,267
who knows?

314
00:16:27,400 --> 00:16:30,400
They might forgive me
once Jessica and I leave.

315
00:16:30,533 --> 00:16:33,833
But I hope you're not
coming back to Hazel.

316
00:16:33,967 --> 00:16:36,233
We're not. She's crazy.

317
00:16:37,700 --> 00:16:39,533
I'm planning to...

318
00:16:39,667 --> 00:16:41,733
file for an annulment.

319
00:16:41,900 --> 00:16:44,033
Why would you suddenly say that?

320
00:16:44,167 --> 00:16:45,533
Because of Felma.

321
00:16:47,100 --> 00:16:49,733
We want us to get
back together.

322
00:16:52,167 --> 00:16:53,933
I still love her.

323
00:16:55,167 --> 00:16:56,833
I know that, silly.

324
00:16:58,300 --> 00:16:59,733
But bro,

325
00:16:59,867 --> 00:17:02,567
I'm confused.

326
00:17:03,333 --> 00:17:05,133
You said...

327
00:17:05,267 --> 00:17:07,700
you'll get your marriage
with Hazel annulled

328
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:11,767
and you'll
get back together with Felma.

329
00:17:11,900 --> 00:17:14,300
But you're leaving now that
you're already with her.

330
00:17:14,433 --> 00:17:15,600
Why?

331
00:17:17,233 --> 00:17:18,833
Of course,

332
00:17:18,967 --> 00:17:21,000
I don't want
to overstay our welcome.

333
00:17:21,133 --> 00:17:24,433
And some people might
take it the wrong way,

334
00:17:24,567 --> 00:17:27,433
especially our kids.

335
00:17:27,567 --> 00:17:28,900
Oh, you have a point there.

336
00:17:29,833 --> 00:17:31,200
That's a good decision.

337
00:17:32,233 --> 00:17:33,933
I'll support you.

338
00:17:34,067 --> 00:17:36,300
But...

339
00:17:36,433 --> 00:17:38,300
the question is,

340
00:17:38,433 --> 00:17:40,867
does Felma still love you?

341
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,733
She no longer does, right?

342
00:17:42,867 --> 00:17:44,333
Well, that's the problem.

343
00:17:44,467 --> 00:17:46,733
I don't know, bro.
Whatever happens, happens.

344
00:17:48,100 --> 00:17:50,367
Once my marriage to Hazel
gets annulled,

345
00:17:52,333 --> 00:17:54,000
I'll pursue her again.

346
00:17:55,167 --> 00:17:57,333
And I'll ask
her to marry me.

347
00:18:06,233 --> 00:18:09,967
What I mean is you only
have the same father.

348
00:18:10,100 --> 00:18:11,400
Half-siblings.

349
00:18:12,600 --> 00:18:14,033
And besides,

350
00:18:14,167 --> 00:18:16,167
you didn't grow up together.

351
00:18:16,300 --> 00:18:17,733
So what do you expect?

352
00:18:17,867 --> 00:18:20,033
They'll welcome
you just like that?

353
00:18:20,167 --> 00:18:22,433
You heard what
Coleen said, right?

354
00:18:22,600 --> 00:18:25,233
She wants your Dad
all to themselves.

355
00:18:25,367 --> 00:18:26,500
Dear,

356
00:18:26,633 --> 00:18:28,433
they'll steal Manuel.

357
00:18:29,433 --> 00:18:31,600
And once they reconcile,

358
00:18:31,733 --> 00:18:33,933
their family
will be whole again.

359
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:35,400
What if...

360
00:18:36,600 --> 00:18:38,367
they ask your Dad to choose?

361
00:18:40,000 --> 00:18:42,200
Dad won't leave me, Mom.

362
00:18:42,333 --> 00:18:43,733
Are you sure?

363
00:18:45,033 --> 00:18:47,033
That's his three children

364
00:18:47,167 --> 00:18:49,900
versus you, who's all alone.

365
00:18:50,033 --> 00:18:51,900
Do you think
he'll choose you?

366
00:18:52,767 --> 00:18:54,467
Dear,

367
00:18:54,600 --> 00:18:55,967
don't let that happen.

368
00:18:57,333 --> 00:19:00,867
Don't let Felma and
Manuel get back together.

369
00:19:01,000 --> 00:19:02,933
Because when that happens,

370
00:19:03,067 --> 00:19:04,900
you'll be pushed aside.

371
00:19:05,833 --> 00:19:08,567
Don't let them build their
family while destroying ours.

372
00:19:10,833 --> 00:19:12,033
Remember,

373
00:19:13,067 --> 00:19:15,067
you and I...

374
00:19:16,767 --> 00:19:18,933
are his only real family.

375
00:19:34,967 --> 00:19:36,067
Dad, please hurry.

376
00:19:36,200 --> 00:19:37,667
- I'm going to be late.
- I'm on it.

377
00:19:37,800 --> 00:19:39,767
I've been trying
to wake you up so early.

378
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,900
- You got up late.
- Yes, you're noisy again.

379
00:19:42,033 --> 00:19:44,467
Yes, we're leaving later today.

380
00:19:44,600 --> 00:19:47,067
Okay, bye.

381
00:19:47,200 --> 00:19:48,833
- Good morning.
- Good morning, Mom.

382
00:19:48,967 --> 00:19:50,867
You're home early.
I thought you'd work overtime?

383
00:19:51,000 --> 00:19:52,567
I rejected it,

384
00:19:52,700 --> 00:19:54,633
so we could eat
breakfast together.

385
00:19:54,767 --> 00:19:56,600
But I got stuck in traffic.

386
00:19:56,733 --> 00:19:59,233
Just bring this with you.

387
00:19:59,367 --> 00:20:00,767
Let's look at it.

388
00:20:02,700 --> 00:20:03,633
Wow.

389
00:20:03,767 --> 00:20:05,800
Too bad.
We're all in a good mood.

390
00:20:05,933 --> 00:20:08,100
Let's do this instead. Later,
can you go to work late?

391
00:20:08,233 --> 00:20:10,467
Then let's eat out.
I'll treat you to a date.

392
00:20:10,600 --> 00:20:13,100
Okay, I'll try. But I don't want
to make a promise.

393
00:20:13,233 --> 00:20:15,167
That's good enough. Game!

394
00:20:15,300 --> 00:20:16,800
Family date!

395
00:20:18,567 --> 00:20:20,300
You should ride on my back
so we can get there faster.

396
00:20:20,433 --> 00:20:20,900
Go on! Hurry!

397
00:20:22,800 --> 00:20:25,033
- There, let's go!
- Wait.

398
00:20:25,167 --> 00:20:27,733
Have I already told you
I love you?

399
00:20:27,867 --> 00:20:29,733
It doesn't seem like it.
And yesterday, too.

400
00:20:29,867 --> 00:20:32,300
You owe me two "I love you".

401
00:20:32,433 --> 00:20:35,633
I love you, Dad. I love you.
I love you!

402
00:20:35,800 --> 00:20:37,967
That was three.

403
00:20:38,100 --> 00:20:40,233
Because I might forget it again.

404
00:20:40,367 --> 00:20:42,100
You're too young, yet you're
already forgetful. Let's go.

405
00:20:42,233 --> 00:20:45,133
- Bye, Mom. I love you!
- Bye, dear. Take care.

406
00:21:13,700 --> 00:21:16,400
<i> I didn't deny it because...</i>

407
00:21:16,533 --> 00:21:18,167
<i> it's true.</i>

408
00:21:18,300 --> 00:21:19,733
<i> I still love Felma.</i>

409
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:22,900
Ma'am Felma,

410
00:21:23,033 --> 00:21:25,433
you wanted to see me?

411
00:21:28,767 --> 00:21:29,800
Ma'am?

412
00:21:32,700 --> 00:21:33,800
Ma'am Felma?

413
00:21:35,200 --> 00:21:38,600
Ma'am Felma!

414
00:21:38,733 --> 00:21:41,000
They said you wanted to see me.

415
00:21:42,900 --> 00:21:44,867
Sorry,

416
00:21:45,000 --> 00:21:47,300
I've got something
on my mind.

417
00:21:47,433 --> 00:21:49,967
You really do look
deep in thought, Ma'am.

418
00:21:51,800 --> 00:21:52,833
Yes.

419
00:21:56,833 --> 00:21:57,933
Angge,

420
00:21:59,767 --> 00:22:03,733
I hope you don't take it
the wrong way, but...

421
00:22:04,767 --> 00:22:07,100
You and your husband separated,
right?

422
00:22:08,167 --> 00:22:09,500
Yes.

423
00:22:11,367 --> 00:22:13,033
I'm just really curious.

424
00:22:15,333 --> 00:22:17,667
It's okay
if you don't want to answer it.

425
00:22:18,967 --> 00:22:20,867
Why did you come back
to your husband?

426
00:22:23,000 --> 00:22:24,833
I love him, Ma'am.

427
00:22:30,133 --> 00:22:33,933
You've defeated me.

428
00:22:34,067 --> 00:22:35,633
That's an exaggeration, Dad.

429
00:22:35,767 --> 00:22:38,067
Are you sure it's your
first time playing this?

430
00:22:38,200 --> 00:22:40,800
Yes, Dad. This is my first time.

431
00:22:40,933 --> 00:22:42,600
Why are you so good already?

432
00:22:42,733 --> 00:22:45,067
It's because
you're a good teacher.

433
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:47,100
See? I've got nothing left.

434
00:22:50,567 --> 00:22:52,867
- Are you cheating?
- Of course not.

435
00:22:53,000 --> 00:22:54,367
It's your turn already.

436
00:23:00,033 --> 00:23:01,933
<i> It's his three children</i>

437
00:23:02,067 --> 00:23:04,200
<i> versus you, who's just one.</i>

438
00:23:04,333 --> 00:23:06,533
<i>Do you really think
he'll choose you?</i>

439
00:23:06,667 --> 00:23:07,667
<i> You...</i>

440
00:23:07,800 --> 00:23:09,033
<i> and I...</i>

441
00:23:09,167 --> 00:23:11,433
<i> are his only real family.</i>

442
00:23:14,833 --> 00:23:16,000
Jessica, come here.

443
00:23:16,133 --> 00:23:18,300
I'll also teach you how to play
Sungka. Come on!

444
00:23:18,433 --> 00:23:20,067
It's okay, Dad.

445
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,900
I'm still checking
something online.

446
00:23:22,067 --> 00:23:23,767
Okay, after that, okay?

447
00:23:23,900 --> 00:23:25,267
This is fun.

448
00:23:31,300 --> 00:23:34,167
Dad, I'll just get
the cookies I baked.

449
00:23:34,300 --> 00:23:35,533
Okay.

450
00:23:39,700 --> 00:23:43,433
Enjoy your little moments
with my Dad

451
00:23:43,567 --> 00:23:45,800
while there's time.

452
00:23:45,933 --> 00:23:47,167
Make the most of it.

453
00:23:48,600 --> 00:23:50,600
What do you mean?

454
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,267
Ma'am.

455
00:24:03,400 --> 00:24:04,367
Felma.

456
00:24:07,033 --> 00:24:08,400
Manuel?

457
00:24:11,333 --> 00:24:13,100
- Can we talk?
- Can we talk?

458
00:24:23,333 --> 00:24:24,467
Here's your order.

459
00:24:24,600 --> 00:24:26,100
Nice.

460
00:24:26,233 --> 00:24:27,600
You didn't have
to bring it here.

461
00:24:27,733 --> 00:24:29,067
Special delivery, huh?

462
00:24:30,833 --> 00:24:32,067
Special delivery?

463
00:24:32,200 --> 00:24:36,400
Yes. Because Ma'am Daisy
already came to pick Tetay up.

464
00:24:39,633 --> 00:24:41,067
We didn't talk about this.

465
00:24:42,567 --> 00:24:43,767
Excuse me.

466
00:24:50,367 --> 00:24:51,667
Why isn't she answering?

467
00:25:00,367 --> 00:25:02,100
Even Tetay isn't answering.

468
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:14,100
Jessica has found an apartment.

469
00:25:16,367 --> 00:25:18,233
So you've finally
made a decision.

470
00:25:20,867 --> 00:25:22,000
Well,

471
00:25:22,133 --> 00:25:23,533
maybe you're right.

472
00:25:24,900 --> 00:25:26,333
Maybe you should leave...

473
00:25:27,233 --> 00:25:29,067
to...

474
00:25:29,200 --> 00:25:31,433
to finally end all this chaos.

475
00:25:35,300 --> 00:25:37,433
But Felma,
I'll come back for you.

476
00:25:37,567 --> 00:25:39,067
I'll just annul my marriage
with Hazel,

477
00:25:39,200 --> 00:25:41,000
and then I'll come back to you.

478
00:25:43,200 --> 00:25:44,600
Felma, you're the one I love.

479
00:25:46,200 --> 00:25:49,333
You were the one I loved
then, you're the one I love now.

480
00:25:49,467 --> 00:25:51,733
You're the one
I'll love forever.

481
00:25:55,367 --> 00:25:56,433
Daisy?

482
00:25:56,567 --> 00:25:57,567
Tetay?

483
00:25:57,700 --> 00:25:59,200
Mon, where's Daisy?

484
00:25:59,333 --> 00:26:02,267
I saw Daisy earlier
carrying luggage.

485
00:26:02,400 --> 00:26:06,500
Jeffrey and Andrea can
never accept this.

486
00:26:06,633 --> 00:26:10,867
I'll prove to them that
it's only you I love.

487
00:26:11,033 --> 00:26:13,733
I thought we would finally
be a happy family.

488
00:26:13,867 --> 00:26:15,633
That we'd all be together.

489
00:26:15,767 --> 00:26:17,900
Why are you taking
me away from Dad?

490
00:26:18,033 --> 00:26:19,833
Dear, where are you going?

491
00:26:19,967 --> 00:26:21,200
In Australia.

492
00:26:21,333 --> 00:26:23,100
Dear, please don't leave me.

493
00:26:23,233 --> 00:26:26,533
I won't force you
if you don't want to.

494
00:26:26,667 --> 00:26:29,033
Felma, don't you
love me anymore?
